rComments: The class is tough, it is not an easy task to work with the large format cameras. but the hard work pays off. Lorraine is extremely helpful and comforting when you are feeling discouraged. She sympathizes with your difficulties and does not grade unfairly for things that are beyond your control. If you work hard, she sees that.

A very nice prof, helpful and understanding. Puts no pressure on you to be perfect. A Prof who actually see's students as people, and actually talks to you. sometimes hard to stay awake because it was so early, but it was actually fun. She understands that some poeple arn't into Photography and give special advise to the hardcore Photographer.

Lorraine will go all out to help you achieve the perfect photo.  She'll find articles to help develope ideas and meet you out of class if you need it.  She is also an extremely interesting photographer with a good sense of humour.  Great prof!

She really loves what she does, so she loves all the work the students do. Shes been told to start marking harder, b/c all her marks are too high. shes really nice and helpful, very positive and helpful.  i definitley recommend her for a teacher, makes even a 4 hour class very enjoyable.

Loraine had a way of explaining something so that even an idiot could understand. If she had been a little harder on her students she would have been the perfect teacher. I can’t believe some of the things I got away with. I don’t think I could have done another project about nature or something relating to it, I just don’t give a sh*t. I’m sad to
